  "body": "# Problem\r\nWhen the user has set `Save password`, going to the `unlock view` can result in an endless loop of sign out>unlock, making it impossible to switch accounts. This scenario is currently counteracted (does not occur), because auth-methods are erased on `Sign out`. However, erasing auth-methods on sign out causes other issues:\r\n- Requiring Keycard to open a Keycard multiaccount, in spite of having set `Don't ask for Keycard`, see #9763\r\n- The user having to re-enable biometric unlock (fingerprint or faceID) without being informed that they are required to do so when they sign out\r\n\r\n## Implementation\r\nTo resolve these issues, allow maintaining the stored auth-method, `Sign out` should go to the `Your keys` (multiaccount overview) screen.\r\n\r\nSee future steps, current key encryption and storage needs to be investigated. If keys are encrypted with the password, rather than a key generated by status-react (as proposed [here](https://docs.google.com/document/d/1IrjvvAuAQbYsr3xqZvXfgAeeyDZRl_x9KRxWnLcwVuI/edit#bookmark=id.h09ezqb1viei)), credentials (password?) might be required. Possibly auth-method is erased to prompt password.\r\n\r\n#### Desired flow\r\nSign out > Select keys to unlock > Unlock screen\r\n![Frame 26](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/35233054/73058376-c2f25f00-3e93-11ea-8265-ff0497ffb046.png)\r\n\r\n## Acceptance Criteria\r\n`Sign out` opens `Your keys`\r\n\r\n## Future Steps\r\n- Depending on how keys are encrypted and stored, create issue to investigate key encryption according to [proposal](https://docs.google.com/document/d/1IrjvvAuAQbYsr3xqZvXfgAeeyDZRl_x9KRxWnLcwVuI/edit#bookmark=id.h09ezqb1viei)\r\n- Depending on whether keys can be encrypted and stored according to proposal, investigate maintaining stored auth-method\r\n",
